    <!-- Narrative introduction -->
    <div class="narrative">
      <p>At the end of a road crossing three kingdoms stands the World City - a metropolis so vast it has its own seasons. Thousands of artisans work there in the same interconnected workshop: blacksmiths, weavers, alchemists, scribes, all under the same titanic roof. The corridors stretch for leagues, the archives occupy entire floors, and yet everything is connected, everything is coherent.</p>
      <p>The City Architect greets you atop the central tower. From here, you can see the immensity of the workshop below.</p>
      <p>"Every village has its forge, its library, its temple. It's simple. It's self-contained. But when a thousand artisans must work together, share their tools, reuse their creations - <strong>a single giant workshop</strong> sometimes becomes more efficient than a thousand separate ones. That's the choice the greatest cities in the world have made. And it's a choice that comes at a price. Let me explain."</p>
    </div>

